  <section>
    <h2>Blockquote Behavior</h2>
    <p>Inside <code>&lt;blockquote&gt;</code>, VB de-emphasizes italic text &mdash; <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;i&gt;</code> become normal-style with <code>font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium)</code>. This prevents double-emphasis, since the blockquote itself is already visually offset.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Italic in blockquote">{{ blockquoteCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Combined Bold + Italic</h2>
    <p>When <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> is nested inside <code>&lt;strong&gt;</code> (or vice versa), VB ensures the combined style renders correctly with <code>font-synthesis: none</code>:</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Combined bold and italic">{{ combinedCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="em and i CSS">{{ emCssCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Some screen readers announce <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> with a change in voice tone or pitch</li>
      <li>This distinguishes it from <code>&lt;i&gt;</code> which is not announced differently</li>
      <li>Nesting <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> increases the degree of emphasis</li>
      <li>Do not rely on emphasis alone to convey critical meaning &mdash; combine with context</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

